<br>
<br>
<DIV class="poemtitle">July in January</DIV><br>
  <div align="center"><img src="images/julyinjanuary.jpg"><br>
  <a class="artistline" href="javascript:goauthor('jones');">art by Pat Jones</a></div><br>
<TABLE><TR><TD>
<br>
<br>
This shortage of snowflakes<br />
contradicts the calendar.<br />
In remote hideaways, bears lie<br />
wide awake, irritable; <br />
along great rivers, ducks and geese<br />
stay put, when right here<br />
there’s food enough<br />
in snowless fields. Saturday night,<br />
with record highs, we open a window, hear<br />
befuddled frogs still piping<br />
their summer chorus<br />
in nearby bogs. Snowshoe hares<br />
in their winter whites; hawk<br />
and owl ruffle the air;<br />
the grass corrupt<br />
with an eerie green. <br /><br>
<br><br>
<a class="byline" href="javascript:goauthor('kimball')">by Don Kimball</a><br><br><br>
</TD></TR></TABLE>
